[{"id":"FT562062","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p>If the block is sliding up section 2, what is the magnitude of the force of friction that is exerted on the block by the incline?</p>","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n<img alt=\"The figure shows a block on an inclined plane. The incline is represented by a right triangle: the base of the triangle is horizontal and the incline is its hypotenuse, at an angle theta with the horizontal base. The block is labeled M and sits on the upper end of the incline. A dashed line perpendicular to the incline divides the incline into 2 equal sections. The upper section closer to the block is labeled Section 1, and the lower section farther from the block is labeled Section 2. \" height=\"209\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/8def7615c465e477175f8a24f1d13a52/original.png\" width=\"300\">\n<p>The inclined plane in the figure above has two sections of equal length and different roughness. The dashed line shows where section 1 ends and section 2 begins. A block of mass M is placed at different locations on the incline. The coefficients of kinetic and static friction between the block and each section are shown in the table below.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"A table with three columns and two rows is shown. The first column is labeled Coefficient of Friction, the second column is labeled Section 1, and the third column is labeled Section 2. The first row reads Static, μs1, μs2 (> μs1). The second row reads Kinetic, μk, 2μk.\" height=\"91\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/e4d23152645838012165e8595e7a9d47/original.png\" width=\"350\"></p>"}],"choicesHtml":["2 <em>μk</em> <em>Mg</em> cos θ","2<em> μk Mg</em> tan θ","<em>Mg</em> sin θ","<em>Mg</em> / tan θ"],"answer":-1}]